# ğŸ§© STAGE 1 â€” Advanced C# + Unity Architecture Patterns

Here you go from â€œwriting scriptsâ€ â†’ to **engineering reusable systems**.

### ğŸ”¹ Topics:

| Concept                                        | Why Itâ€™s Needed                             | Example                                  |
| ---------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| **ScriptableObject Architecture**              | Data-driven systems, reusable across scenes | Item stats, weapon configs, enemy data   |
| **Event Bus / Observer Pattern**               | Decouple systems cleanly                    | UI listens to health events              |
| **Dependency Injection (Zenject / Extenject)** | Cleaner modular systems                     | Replace player logic easily              |
| **Interfaces + Polymorphism**                  | Flexibility in gameplay systems             | `IInteractable` for all pickable objects |
| **Finite State Machines (FSM)**                | Control states logically                    | Player: Idle â†’ Walk â†’ Attack             |
| **Behavior Trees**                             | Smart AI systems                            | Enemies deciding how to act              |
| **Service Locator / GameManager architecture** | Manage cross-scene services                 | Audio, Input, Save System                |

